wondering if MethodHandle doesn't really assist with coverage either. If I go with reflection invoke, would the stack then include NativeMethodAccessor and subsequently reference `BCECGOST`? I need to investigate these options further!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_a9wnwB6sxRD7CH68PHSdEdMw|fc_0d32ede2925cc8e20169fbd38e97f48197ba3076057e625f0c", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bcprov-jdk18on/1.77/src/test/java/org_bouncycastle/bcprov_jdk18on/BCECGOST3410PrivateKeyTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;", "newText": "import java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;"}, {"oldText": "        RecordingObjectOutputStream outputStream = new RecordingObjectOutputStream();\n\n        WRITE_OBJECT.invokeExact(privateKey, (ObjectOutputStream)outputStream);\n\n        byte[] encoded = privateKey.getEncoded();\n        assertThat((byte[])outputStream.writtenObject()).isEqualTo(encoded);\n\n        BCECGOST3410PrivateKey restored = new BCECGOST3410PrivateKey(\n                new ECPrivateKeySpec(BigInteger.ONE, parameters));\n        ReplayingObjectInputStream inputStream = new ReplayingObjectInputStream(encoded);\n\n        READ_OBJECT.invokeExact(restored, (ObjectInputStream)inputStream);", "newText": "        EncodingObjectOutputStream outputStream = new EncodingObjectOutputStream();\n\n        WRITE_OBJECT.invokeExact(privateKey, (ObjectOutputStream)outputStream);\n\n        byte[] encoded = privateKey.getEncoded();\n        assertThat(readEncodedObject(outputStream.toByteArray())).isEqualTo(encoded);\n\n        BCECGOST3410PrivateKey restored = new BCECGOST3410PrivateKey(\n                new ECPrivateKeySpec(BigInteger.ONE, parameters));\n        EncodingObjectInputStream inputStream = new EncodingObjectInputStream(outputStream.toByteArray());\n\n        READ_OBJECT.invokeExact(restored, (ObjectInputStream)inputStream);"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class RecordingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private Object writtenObject;\n\n        private RecordingObjectOutputStream() throws Exception {\n            super();\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultWriteObject() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected void writeObjectOverride(Object object) {\n            writtenObject = object;\n        }\n\n        private Object writtenObject() {\n            return writtenObject;\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class ReplayingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private final Object object;\n\n        private ReplayingObjectInputStream(Object object) throws Exception {\n            super();\n            this.object = object;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultReadObject() {\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        protected Object readObjectOverride() {\n            return object;\n        }\n    }\n", "newText": "    private static byte[] readEncodedObject(byte[] serializedObject) throws Exception {\n        try (ObjectInputStream inputStream = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedObject))) {\n            return (byte[])inputStream.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodingObjectOutputStream extends ObjectOutputStream {\n        private final ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream;\n\n        private EncodingObjectOutputStream() throws Exception {\n            this(new ByteArrayOutputStream());\n        }\n\n        private EncodingObjectOutputStream(ByteArrayOutputStream outputStream) throws Exception {\n            super(outputStream);\n            this.outputStream = outputStream;\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultWriteObject() {\n        }\n\n        private byte[] toByteArray() {\n            return outputStream.toByteArray();\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class EncodingObjectInputStream extends ObjectInputStream {\n        private EncodingObjectInputStream(byte[] serializedObject) throws Exception {\n            super(new ByteArrayInputStream(serializedObject));\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void defaultReadObject() {\n        }\n    }\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 43185, "output": 2901, "cacheRead": 6656, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 52742, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778111340562, "responseId": "resp_0d32ede2925cc8e20169fbd36ea4d48197862073ef3c909868"}}
